title: PPPP’s Qaim Ali Shah wins PS-26 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Syed Qaim Ali Shah has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-26 Khairpur-I by securing 63,686 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Imam Bux Phulpoto of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged 19,041 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 43.95%.
